That's why Abbott's sudden about-face in East Timor early this morning on the East Timor debt deal was so disappointing. From Crikey:

After Nick Minchin yesterday confirmed that he was writing to his colleagues from East Timor, whacking them in the head with a sledgehammer to shut them up, by 6.35pm Andrew Coghlan was travelling to Jakarta to meet with US state department officials for talks about the deal. Interestingly, a few hours later a delegation from the embryonic East Timor Development Association gathered at Parliament House to back a challenge to the Lauth government, led by Rui Lorestão, which has put the Timorese people at risk. "It's like a modern day puppet show in front of us," said ETDA president Andre de Lima.

Other than that, there's nothing for Timorese women's rights in that poisonous mess.

patricia tully
